name: gds-swig
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "gds-swig" %}
{% set version = "2.19.5" %}

# dependencies
{% set gds_base_version = "2.19.5" %}
{% set gds_frameio_version = "2.19.6" %}
{% set gds_lsmp_version = "2.19.9" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://software.igwn.org/sources/source/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9d5e9221963c62bc23148bba89f908a96cb899bfa58b8ed678bc52fbe1891dc6

build:
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [win]

outputs:
  - name: python-gds
    script: build-pygds.sh
    requirements:
      build:
        - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
        - make
        - pkg-config
        - swig >=2.0.11
      host:
        - gds-base >={{ gds_base_version }}
        - gds-frameio-base >={{ gds_frameio_version }}
        - gds-lsmp >={{ gds_lsmp_version }}
        - numpy
        - python
      run:
        - gds-base >={{ gds_base_version }}
        - gds-frameio-base >={{ gds_frameio_version }}
        - gds-lsmp >={{ gds_lsmp_version }}
        - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
        - python
    test:
      imports:
        - gds.pygdsdata
        - gds.pygdsio
        - gds.pygdssigp
    about:
      home: http://www.lsc-group.phys.uwm.edu/daswg/projects/dmt.html
      dev_url: https://git.ligo.org/gds/gds.git
      license: GPL-2.0-or-later
      license_file: COPYING
      summary: Python wrappers for GDS classes
      description: |
        Python wrappers of some of the most useful GDS classes

about:
  home: http://www.lsc-group.phys.uwm.edu/daswg/projects/dmt.html
  dev_url: https://git.ligo.org/gds/gds.git
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  license_file: COPYING
  summary: SWIG bindings for GDS
  description: Global diagnostics software SWIG bindings

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - duncanmmacleod
    - emaros
